  "prompt": "How do I recover a Yahoo hacked email address?",
  "response": "If you suspect that your Yahoo email account has been hacked, you should take immediate steps to secure it. Here's a guide to help you recover your hacked Yahoo email account:\n\n1. **Change Your Password:**\n   - Go to the Yahoo Sign-In Helper page at https://login.yahoo.com/forgot.\n   - Select \"Forgotten password?\" and follow the prompts to reset your password.\n   - Make sure to create a strong password that includes a mix of uppercase and lowercase letters, numbers, and special characters.\n\n2. **Check Account Information:**\n   - After regaining access, review your account information to ensure that it hasn't been altered. Check your recovery email and phone number, and update them if necessary.\n   - Go to your Yahoo account settings, and ensure all recovery options are correct and secure.\n\n3. **Review Recent Activity:**\n   - Check the recent activity on your account to identify any unauthorized logins.\n   - In your Yahoo account, navigate to \"Account Info\" and then \"Recent activity\" to review logins and access locations.\n\n4. **Update Security Settings:**\n   - Implement two-step verification for your Yahoo account. This adds an extra layer of security by requiring a verification code in addition to your password when accessing your account from an unknown device.\n\n5. **Scan for Malware:**\n   - Run a complete malware and virus scan on your computer or device to ensure that it is secure and not compromised.\n\n6. **Notify Contacts:**\n   - Consider notifying your contacts that your account was compromised, especially if you suspect that spam emails were sent from your account.\n\n7. **Contact Yahoo Support:**\n   - If you\u2019re unable to recover your account with the steps above, you may need to contact Yahoo Support for assistance. Look for relevant support options on their help page.\n\n8. **Stay Vigilant:**\n   - Be cautious of phishing emails and suspicious links or attachments in the future. Regularly update your passwords and security settings to protect your account.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to recover and secure your hacked Yahoo email account.",
